Author: The Anh Tran <trantheanh.ktmt@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jul 1 19:09:13 2026 +0900

    common.sh: build serve args as an array to preserve space-containing values
    
    common_serve_args echoed its flags as a single string and launch_vllm
    re-split that string with `read -a`, which word-splits on whitespace and
    ignores quoting. Any flag whose value contains a space (e.g. a JSON value
    like --compilation-config '{"cudagraph_mode": "PIECEWISE"}') was broken into
    two tokens, so vLLM received truncated, invalid JSON and refused to start.
    
    Populate a COMMON_SERVE_ARGS array instead and splice it in directly, so each
    argument stays a single element regardless of internal spaces. The
    --served-model-name flag is preserved.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

